# Enterprise Cash Reconciliation Desk — Implementation Plan

## Executive Summary

Implement an Enterprise Cash Reconciliation Desk as an **independent subsystem** within the existing Investment Banking Operations Simulator. The system consumes data from two independent sources (Trade Objects → Ledger Items, SWIFT Statements → Statement Items), stores both in a single `reconciliation_items` collection, and provides a user-driven manual matching workstation with automatic allocation of 20 settled trades (40 reconciliation rows).

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Existing modules are partially implemented.** The `ReconciliationItem` model, `reconciliationService`, `matchingEngine`, `ledgerImporter`, `statementImporter`, and `reconciliation-desk` frontend page already exist on `Swift_Main`. However, they have several architectural violations that must be corrected:
> 1. `statementImporter.js` enriches Statement items from Trade Object (violates data independence)
> 2. `matchingEngine.js` performs auto-matching (must be manual user-driven)
> 3. No allocation service exists (20 settled trades → 40 rows)
> 4. No user-driven match selection in frontend
> 5. No lifecycle auto-generation for insufficient settled trades

