## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Statement Data Independence Fix**: The current `statementImporter.js` (lines 43-60) populates Statement items with trade-level data (`trade.tradeDate`, `trade.tradeRef`, `trade.underlyer`, `trade.entity`, `trade.product`, `trade.productType`, `trade.amount`, `trade.currency`). Per requirements, Statement items must contain **ONLY** data genuinely present inside the generated SWIFT message. This will be corrected — trade-specific fields (`tradeDate`, `itemRef1-6`) will be set to `null` on Statement items.

> [!WARNING]
> **Matching Engine Change**: The current `matchingEngine.js` performs automatic batch matching. This will be replaced with **manual user-driven matching** where the user selects one LEDGER + one STATEMENT row and clicks "Match". The auto-matching `runMatching()` function will be removed from the UI but preserved in the engine for potential future use.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Auto-Generation of Settled Trades**: When a user enters the Reconciliation Desk and fewer than 20 settled trades exist, the system will auto-generate additional trades and run them through the **complete lifecycle** (Trade → MO → Confirmation → Settlement → SWIFT → Statement). These trades will be created with `currentStatus: "SETTLED"` and `assignedTo: null` so they never appear in operational queues.

