## Proposed Changes

### Component 1: Reconciliation Repository Layer (NEW)

Introduces the dedicated Repository/Query Service abstraction between all reconciliation services and MongoDB. All CRUD operations on `reconciliation_items` flow through this single gateway.

#### [NEW] [reconciliationRepository.js](file:///d:/SBG/ilabs1/src/engine/reconciliationRepository.js)

- Central data access layer for `reconciliation_items` collection
- Encapsulates all MongoDB queries (find, create, update, aggregate)
- Methods: `createItem()`, `findByItemId()`, `findByFilters()`, `updateMatchStatus()`, `countByQuery()`, `getStats()`, `getMatchPairs()`, `findByTradeRef()`, `findByMatchId()`, `allocateItems()`
- All existing services (reconService, matchingEngine, ledgerImporter, statementImporter) will be refactored to use this repository
- Future-proofs for partial matching, one-to-many, suspense items, TLM-style workflows

