### Component 2: Statement Importer Fix (CRITICAL)

#### [MODIFY] [statementImporter.js](file:///d:/SBG/ilabs1/src/engine/statementImporter.js)

**Why**: Current implementation violates data independence by enriching Statement items from Trade Object. Lines 43-60 use `trade.tradeDate`, `trade.tradeRef`, `trade.underlyer`, `trade.entity`, `trade.product`, `trade.productType`.

**What changes**:
- `amount` → Use ONLY `swiftMessage.amount` (remove `|| trade.amount` fallback)
- `currency` → Use ONLY `swiftMessage.currency` (remove `|| trade.currency` fallback)
- `tradeDate` → Set to `null` (not present in SWIFT message)
- `valueDate` → Use ONLY `swiftMessage.valueDate` (remove `|| trade.valueDate` fallback)
- `reconDesk` → Derive from SWIFT message BIC geography (not from `trade.foRegion`)
- `itemRef1` through `itemRef6` → ALL set to `null` (trade-specific data not in SWIFT)
- `itemType` → Derive from SWIFT `paymentDirection` field instead of `trade.direction`
- Keep ref1-ref8 SWIFT extractors unchanged (they correctly use SWIFT data)
- Refactor to use `ReconciliationRepository` for persistence

**Impact**: Statement items will have fewer populated fields, making reconciliation harder (as intended — user must investigate).

