## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests

After implementation, a verification script will:

1. Create 100 trades with `currentStatus: "SETTLED"`
2. Generate SWIFT messages for all 100
3. Verify:
   - Every trade has exactly ONE Ledger item (`source: "LEDGER"`, `itemRef1: tradeRef`)
   - Every settled trade with SWIFT has exactly ONE Statement item (`source: "STATEMENT"`)
   - Statement items NEVER contain trade-only fields (`tradeDate`, `itemRef1-6` are all `null`)
   - Ledger items NEVER contain SWIFT-only fields (`ref1-8` are all `null`)
   - No duplicate `itemId` values
   - No duplicate `matchId` values
   - Allocation returns exactly 20 trades = 40 rows

### Manual Verification

- Navigate to Reconciliation Desk → verify allocation flow
- Select 1 LEDGER + 1 STATEMENT → click Match → verify match succeeds/fails correctly
- Verify matched items show same Match ID
- Verify no auto-matching occurs
- Verify Statement items have no trade-enriched data

